Some of my current and past projects, arranged from most to least recent.

My research projects span bioinformatics, data mining, and machine learning, and use mostly python, bash, and sometimes R. My web projects are mostly full-stack, built with JavaScript and occasionally Flask. Open source projects are linked to GitHub.

Research

  • Clustering SQL queries for structure and semantics. Current.

  • ClonArch: Visualizing the spatial clonal architecture of tumors.
    To appear in ISMB 2020. [Preprint]

  • Tasty-search: Search engine feedback for difficult queries – designed to incorporate explicit user feedback into supervised learning-to-rank algorithms. 2019.

  • Developing a pipeline for cancer genome analysis – following GATK best practices for alignment of raw FASTA files, SNV calling, somatic CNA calling, and retrieving mutational signatures. 2019.

  • Weakly-supervised classification of GitHub repositories (slides) – automated labeling of GitHub repositories using raw readmes, code files, and additional metadata. 2019.
  • Primary tumor detection – predicting tumor origin sites from DNA methylation and microRNA expression profiles. (Tensorflow). 2019.
  • Study Genie – a web-based study tool that explores the role of collaborative learning and note-taking on student performance in computer science courses.
    ACM SIGCSE 2018.
  • Cell to cell communication systems for genetic circuitry – characterizing crosstalk in bacterial homoserine lactone signaling systems. (Wet lab: cloning, primer design). 2017. Gold medal, 2 awards, 2 nominations at iGEM 2016; published in PLOS ONE

Web

  • Stock Spy – analyze historical trends for any stock based on contextual, time-relevant news. HackIllinois 2020.

  • Personal Website (demo) – version 1 of personal website with a heavier design-focus, using Bootstrap. Compatible across desktop, laptop, tablet, and mobile. 2018.

  • Perfect Fit – a Firefox web extension that updates your clothing size for different shopping websites. 2018. Judge’s Pick at CodeAda 2018, University of Illinois!

  • Voice and tone guide – a Wordpress theme that helps clients develop better content by displaying short, helpful brand tips. 2017.

  • Burger Builder (demo) – an intuitive and simple web application where you can craft the burger of your dreams! (jQuery, HTML/CSS). SWHacks 2017.

See more miscellaneous projects on my GitHub!
